  "ProductOverview": {
    "Summary": "OpenClinic GA is an open source integrated hospital information management system covering management of administrative, financial, clinical, lab, x-ray, pharmacy, meals distribution, and other data. Extensive statistical and reporting capabilities.",
    "Description": "This system is a highly customizable health information platform with integrated billing (supporting Central African, East African, and Peruvian insurance schemes), clinical coding (ICD-10, ICPC-2, SNOMED CT, LOINC, RxNorm), and comprehensive modules for patient administration, human resources, scheduling, pharmacy, laboratory, imaging, and pathology. It supports advanced statistics on mortality, co-morbidity, and care costs, as well as multimedia records, fingerprint identification, drug interaction checks, and mobile access with barcode scanning. It also offers HL7 integration with lab analyzers, efficient database performance, and multilingual capabilities.",
    "PrimaryFunctionality": "",
    "Users": "All health facility staff",
